 ‘protection, shelter’ or ‘guard’. Compare   Waring  .","English and Irish (of Norman origin): habitational name from La Varrenne in Seine-Maritime, France, named with a Gaulish element probably descriptive of alluvial land or sandy soil. This was the name of a major Norman family after the Conquest. In Ireland, this name has been Gaelicized as <b>Bharain</b>.","Irish: adopted as an English form of Gaelic <b>Ó Murnáin</b> (see   Murnane  ,   Warner  )."]}]},{"name":"Ella","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Of Germanic origin, introduced to Britain by the Normans. It was originally a short form of any of various compound names containing <i>ali</i> ‘other, foreign’ (  compare  Eleanor  ). It is now often taken to be a variant or pet form of   Ellen .  It was famously borne by the American jazz singer Ella Fitzgerald (  1917–1996 ), and has become increasingly popular in Britain since the 1990s."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705185,"age":1,"year":"1106","julianDay":2125018,"title":"The Battle of Tichebray","description":"King Henry I defeated and captured his brother, Robert of Normandy, at the Battle of Tinchebray in 1106. Robert remained in captivity until his death in 1134.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705187,"age":110,"year":"1215","julianDay":2164830,"title":"Magna Carta","description":"King John of England agreed to a charter of rights called the Magna Carta. The document was originally drafted by the Archbishop of Canterbury to establish peace between King John and a group of rebel barons. The Magna Carta was completed in 1215 and is now considered to be one of the greatest constitutional documents of all time.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/education/medieval/magna-carta/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Magna Carta","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705188,"age":119,"year":"1224","julianDay":2168117,"title":"France Declares War on England","description":"France declared war on England as Louis VIII of France attacked Poitou and northern Gascony.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"Lady Ella de Warrene was born about 1105, in Upper Hopton, Yorkshire, England. She married Godric FitzKetelborn before 1125, in England. They were the parents of at least 1 son. She died in England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"um 1105–":"umbes 1105–Surnud","1103–Male":"1103–Surnud","1113–Male":"1113–Surnud","1140–1194":"1140–1194","1105–Female":"1105–Surnud","1106":"1106","before 1125":"enne 1125","1215":"1215","1105":"1105","1224":"1224","1103":"1103","1113":"1113","1140":"1140","1194":"1194","um 1105":"umbes 1105","Hopton, Yorkshire, England":"Yorkshire, England","Upper Hopton, Yorkshire, England":"Upper Hopton, Yorkshire, England","England":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"um 1105–":"noin 1105–Kuollut","1103–Male":"1103–Kuollut","1113–Male":"1113–Kuollut","1140–1194":"1140–1194","1105–Female":"1105–Kuollut","1106":"1106","before 1125":"ennen vuotta 1125","1215":"1215","1105":"1105","1224":"1224","1103":"1103","1113":"1113","1140":"1140","1194":"1194","um 1105":"noin 1105","Hopton, Yorkshire, England":"Yorkshire, England","Upper Hopton, Yorkshire, England":"Upper Hopton, Yorkshire, England","England":"Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"um 1105–":"environ 1105–Décédée","1103–Male":"1103–Décédé","1113–Male":"1113–Décédé","1140–1194":"1140–1194","1105–Female":"1105–Décédée","1106":"1106","before 1125":"avant 1125","1215":"1215","1105":"1105","1224":"1224","1103":"1103","1113":"1113","1140":"1140","1194":"1194","um 1105":"environ 1105","Hopton, Yorkshire, England":"Everwyck, Angleterre","Upper Hopton, Yorkshire, England":"Upper Hopton, Everwyck, Angleterre","England":"Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Lady Ella de Warrene est née environ 1105, à Upper Hopton, Everwyck, Angleterre. Elle a épousé Godric FitzKetelborn avant 1125, à Angleterre. Ils ont eu au moins 1 fils. Elle est décédée à Angleterre, Royaume-Uni."},"de"